// Adversarial: SpeedBoost(1.05) fires on the global Death trigger — meaning every cell
// or bolt destruction applies a 1.05x multiplier to the bolt's ActiveSpeedBoosts.
// Dense layout is chosen deliberately: it maximises simultaneous multi-cell destruction
// events from a single bolt pass-through. If the Death bridge fires multiple times per
// single RequestCellDestroyed event (e.g., due to duplicate message dispatch or a
// for-loop over all entities that re-enters the same entity), multipliers compound
// within a single fixed-update tick: 1.05^N overflows BoltMaxSpeed quickly.
// If each individual cell impact in a piercing chain generates a separate Death event,
// a single bolt pass through 8 cells fires SpeedBoost 8 times: 1.05^8 ≈ 1.48x.
// BoltSpeedAccurate is the primary detector. NoNaN guards against floating-point
// corruption from very large velocity magnitudes. NoEntityLeaks ensures no orphaned
// SpeedBoost component entries accumulate on destroyed entities.
// 5000 frames at moderate chaos gives enough cell destruction events to expose both
// single-event double-fire and multi-cell chain-fire patterns.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 4271,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(ActiveBolts, When(Death, Fire(SpeedBoost((multiplier: 1.05))))),
    ],
)
